      AlpInvest Partners builds long-term, meaningful partnerships with market leaders.
    
Fund Investments


    The firm's Fund Investments team takes a long-term investment perspective—analyzing
    the global economic trends affecting private equity. Operating in Amsterdam, New
    York, and Hong Kong, the team manages an annual allocation of approximately €800 million with total commitments of over €33 billion (as of December 31, 2015). The Fund Investments team
    has over 140 core general partnership relationships worldwide and is a proactive
    partner across the full spectrum of the private equity market, including:



Global Large Buyouts
Middle-Market, Lower Middle-Market, and Growth Buyouts
Venture Capital
Mezzanine
Distressed Securities
Secondary
Clean Tech




    The Fund Investments team follows a deliberate allocation process: top-down segment
    analysis and bottom-up general manager selection. Twice a year the investment team
    conducts a top-down analysis of the general characteristics, size, and growth of
    all private equity market segments. Once favorable segments are identified, the
    investment team then seeks to identify the best-in-class general partners based
    on the team's desired geography, industry focus, and stage of life focus.






