AlpInvest Partners B.V.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 12:09 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of AlpInvest Partners B.V.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
AlpInvest Partners B.V. is an investment firm specializing in direct, fund of fund, secondary investments, secondary purchases, secondary indirect investment, and co-investments investments. It seeks to invest in private equity and venture capital direct and fund investments, and mezzanine transactions. For direct investments, the firm seeks in invest in expansions, restructurings, management buyouts, management buyins, seed/start up, early venture, mid venture, and mezzanine transactions including leveraged buyouts, recapitalizations, and late stage growth financings. In case of direct investments, serves as co-investor alongside another global "private equity" fund that acts as lead invest...
AlpInvest Partners B.V. is an investment firm specializing in direct, fund of fund, secondary investments, secondary purchases, secondary indirect investment, and co-investments investments. It seeks to invest in private equity and venture capital direct and fund investments, and mezzanine transactions. For direct investments, the firm seeks in invest in expansions, restructurings, management buyouts, management buyins, seed/start up, early venture, mid venture, and mezzanine transactions including leveraged buyouts, recapitalizations, and late stage growth financings. In case of direct investments, serves as co-investor alongside another global "private equity" fund that acts as lead investor. It makes majority private equity investments in Belgian, Dutch, German and Luxembourg based companies. For its co-investments, the firm invests in leveraged buyouts and growth capital transactions in both the middle-market and large buyout segments of the market. The firm seeks to make fund investments across the spectrum of private equity market, including buyouts (growth, lower middle market, middle market, large, and later stage buyouts); venture capital; mezzanine; distressed securities; secondary; sustainable energy; and other specialty funds. The firms secondary fund investment transactions include sale of limited partnership interests, spin out, stapled secondary or primary, portfolio restructuring including securitizations and joint ventures, and secondary direct. It invests in manufacturing, business and technology services, life sciences, natural resources, information and communication technology, media, finance and insurance, retail, trade and services, production, and healthcare sectors. Within equity and mezzanine co-investments, it seeks to invest in industrials, financials, materials, consumer discretionary, consumer staple, energy, information technology, and telecommunications sectors. The firm seeks to invest in Asia, Europe, United States, and the rest of the world including South America, Latin American, and Australia. For mezzanine investments, it seeks to investments in primarily in Europe and the United States. For fund investments, the firm invests in pension funds in Canada and Europe and also in European, United States, and Israeli funds. It seeks to allocate between €10 million ($13.72 million) to €500 million ($685.83 million) per fund investment. For its secondary transactions, the firm acquires and restructures portfolios of private equity assets ranging between €1 million ($1.37 million) and to over €1 billion ($1.37 billion). The firm prefers to target technology and life sciences companies throughout Europe, North America, and Asia with transaction values ranging between €10 million($13.72 million) and €250 million ($342.92 million) in a single company. It plays the co-investment role broadly from pure syndication to co-sponsor positions. For later stage co-investments, the firm invests between €10 million ($13.72 million) and €100 million ($137.17 million), but has a preference for transactions between €20 million ($27.43 million) and €60 million ($82.30 million). It does not seek to lead transactions. It also engages in mezzanine with commitment up to €100 million ($137.17 million) in a single transaction. The firm seeks to invest upto €75 million ($102.87 million) in each individual transaction with average investment size of €35 million ($48.01 million). It makes individual mezzanine investments between €20 million ($27.43 million) and €40 million ($54.87 million) and does mezzanine co-investments between €10 million ($13.72 million) and €25 million ($34.29 million). The firm seeks to invest 80 percent of its capital in private equity funds, either directly or through 'secondary' transactions. AlpInvest Partners B.V. was founded in 1999 and is based in Amsterdam, Netherlands with additional offices across United States, Asia, and Europe. As of July 1, 2011, AlpInvest Partners B.V. operates as a subsidiary of The Carlyle Group LP.
Detailed Description


